---
import '../styles/global.css';

const effectiveDate = 'June 8, 2026';
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
		<meta
			name="description"
			content="Terms of service for PaperBright Text Editor, a browser-based writing app with optional Google Drive live save."
		/>
		<title>Terms of Service | PaperBright Text Editor</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<main class="mx-auto flex min-h-screen w-full max-w-3xl flex-col gap-4 px-4 py-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
			<header class="theme-panel flex items-center justify-between gap-3 rounded-lg border border-line bg-white/90 px-4 py-3 shadow-sm">
				<a class="flex min-w-0 items-center gap-3 text-inherit no-underline" href="/">
					<div class="paperbright-logo flex h-10 w-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-ink text-paper" aria-hidden="true">
						<svg width="25" height="25" viewBox="0 0 25 25" fill="none" role="img">
							<path d="M7 3.5h8.2L20 8.3V21H7V3.5Z" fill="white" />
							<path d="M15.2 3.5V8.3H20" fill="#dbeafe" />
							<path d="M10 12.2h7" stroke="#0a0a0a" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" />
							<path d="M10 15.8h5.2" stroke="#0a0a0a" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" />
							<path d="M7 3.5h8.2L20 8.3V21H7V3.5Z" stroke="white" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linejoin="round" />
							<path d="M6.2 18.8c3.2-1.2 6.8-1.2 10 0" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" />
						</svg>
					</div>
					<div>
						<p class="theme-muted text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-muted">PaperBright</p>
						<p class="text-lg font-semibold leading-tight">Terms of Service</p>
					</div>
				</a>
				<a class="rounded-lg border border-line bg-white px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-inherit no-underline" href="/">Open editor</a>
			</header>

			<article class="theme-panel rounded-lg border border-line bg-white/95 p-5 leading-7 shadow-sm sm:p-7">
				<p class="theme-muted text-sm text-muted">Effective date: {effectiveDate}</p>
				<h1 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold">Terms of Service</h1>
				<p class="mt-4">
					These terms apply when you use PaperBright Text Editor. By using the app, you agree to use it responsibly and only for
					lawful purposes.
				</p>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">Your content</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">
					You keep ownership of the documents, notes, file names, and fonts you use with PaperBright. You are responsible for the
					content you write, import, export, or save to Google Drive.
				</p>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">Local editor behavior</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">
					PaperBright is a browser editor. Drafts and settings may be stored in your browser storage on the device and browser you
					use. Clearing browser storage may remove local drafts and preferences.
				</p>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">Google Drive live save</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">
					Google Drive connection is optional. If you connect it, PaperBright uses your permission to create or update files through
					the limited <code>drive.file</code> scope. You can revoke access from your Google Account at any time.
				</p>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">Acceptable use</h2>
				<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
					<li>Do not use PaperBright to violate laws or the rights of others.</li>
					<li>Do not attempt to disrupt, reverse engineer, overload, or abuse the service.</li>
					<li>Do not upload fonts or content unless you have the rights needed to use them.</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">Third-party services</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">
					PaperBright depends on third-party services including Vercel for hosting and Google for optional sign-in and Drive access.
					Those services may have their own terms and policies.
				</p>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">No warranties</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">
					PaperBright is provided as is and as available. The app may change, pause, or stop working, and no guarantee is made that
					local drafts or Drive saves will always be available.
				</p>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">Limitation of liability</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">
					To the maximum extent allowed by law, PaperBright and its maintainers are not liable for lost content, lost profits,
					interruption, or other damages related to use of the app.
				</p>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">Changes</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">These terms may be updated as PaperBright changes. The effective date will show when the terms were last updated.</p>

				<h2 class="mt-7 text-xl font-semibold">Contact</h2>
				<p class="mt-3">
					For questions, open an issue at
					<a class="font-medium text-signal underline" href="https://github.com/MindMatrix-07/PaperBright">MindMatrix-07/PaperBright</a>.
				</p>
			</article>
		</main>
	</body>
</html>
